Iterator invalidation. If we didn&#x27;t have that rule you could write this:<p><pre><code>    let mut vector = ~[ 1, 2, 3, 4, 5 ];
    for vector.each_mut |x| {
    //                   ^ mutable reference
        for 5.times {
            vector.pop();
    //      ~~~~~^ mutable reference
        }
        println((*x).to_str()); // segfault: invalidated iterator
    }</code></pre>
